<h1>Notes on the update</h1>
<p>
If the app is installed on multiple systems in the domain,
make sure to update all Keycloak installations to the same
app version to ensure proper operation of Keycloak.
</p>
<p>
Please see the <a href="http://docs.software-univention.de/keycloak-app/latest/changelog.html">
Keycloak app changelog</a> for detailed information about the changes and bugfixes.
</p>
<p>
<b>Version: 21.1.0-ucs1</b>
<ul>
    <li>
      The UCR variable <strong>ucs/server/sso/virtualhost</strong> has been replaced by <strong>keycloak/apache/config</strong>.
      In case <strong>ucs/server/sso/virtualhost</strong> variable was used to disable the UCS apache configuration for keycloak,
      set <strong>keycloak/apache/config=true</strong> before the update.
    </li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
<b>Version: 21.0.1-ucs1</b>
<ul>
    <li>
      From this version on the keycloak app requires a CPU that supports the microarchitecture level x86-64-v2 (see <a href="https://help.univention.com/t/21420">help.univention.de</a> for more information)
    </li>
    <li>
      Accessing the <i>userinfo</i> endpoint now requires <i>openid</i> to be specified in the list of requested scopes. See this upstream issue <a href="https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/14184">https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/14184</a>.
    </li>
</ul>
</p>
